title: Khudobin stops 34 shots as Ducks beat Wild 4-1 for 1st win
text: Khudobin stops 34 shots as Ducks beat Wild 4-1 for 1st win Monday, 19 October 2015 (10 minutes ago) Anton Khudobin rebounded from a rough outing with 34 saves, and the Anaheim Ducks got goals from Cam Fowler, Rickard Rakell and Mike Santorelli to beat the Minnesota Wild 4-1 on Sunday night for their first victory of the season.
